\[\arcsin (\sin 7x) = 7 \left(x - \frac{2 \pi}{7} \right) = 7x - 2 \pi.\]The first three terms become $x,$ $\pi - 2x,$ $7x - 2 \pi.$  If these form a geometric progression, then
